1
00:00:00,270 --> 00:00:02,569
If he committed suicide because
he couldn't endure the pressure,

2
00:00:02,569 --> 00:00:04,440
it'll be a shock to not only
to the religious community,

3
00:00:04,509 --> 00:00:05,809
but to the public as well.

4
00:00:05,809 --> 00:00:07,450
What's the occasion for your smile?

5
00:00:31,140 --> 00:00:32,170
Dae Young.

6
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:34,640
Dae Young, are you okay?

7
00:00:34,969 --> 00:00:36,009
Dae Young!

8
00:00:46,079 --> 00:00:47,219
Swans?

9
00:00:50,460 --> 00:00:51,490
Come on.

10
00:00:55,630 --> 00:00:56,630
Dae Young.

11
00:00:58,729 --> 00:01:00,329
Darn it, he's here again.

12
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:05,099
What's wrong with him?
Who did this to him?

13
00:01:07,969 --> 00:01:09,239
Did you just...

14
00:01:10,040 --> 00:01:11,540
How could a priest do this?

15
00:01:11,939 --> 00:01:13,579
Then what about you guys?

16
00:01:14,650 --> 00:01:16,510
Sexually molesting a female
churchgoer and embezzling offertory?

17
00:01:17,319 --> 00:01:18,849
You should've at least
made it sound real.

18
00:01:19,079 --> 00:01:20,650
How could you make up a story
so insincerely?

19
00:01:20,790 --> 00:01:21,849
What do you mean?

20
00:01:22,349 --> 00:01:25,189
It's the accurate result of
the secret investigation.

21
00:01:25,359 --> 00:01:26,959
You don't know what
"monsignor" is, do you?

22
00:01:26,959 --> 00:01:28,189
(Monsignor is an honorific form
of address granted to elder clergy.)

23
00:01:28,189 --> 00:01:30,730
It's a title given to the holiest
and honorable clergy.

24
00:01:31,459 --> 00:01:33,900
Father Lee was granted such title
by the Pope himself.

25
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:35,129
How could you dishonor
a man like him?

26
00:01:35,299 --> 00:01:37,700
Whatever that word means,

27
00:01:37,939 --> 00:01:39,700
if he committed crimes,

28
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:40,810
then he should receive punishment.

29
00:01:40,969 --> 00:01:42,170
Just tell me the reason then.

30
00:01:43,010 --> 00:01:44,439
What do you gain from this?

31
00:01:45,379 --> 00:01:47,549
Why would you dishonor
such an old and weak priest?

32
00:01:48,310 --> 00:01:49,409
Is it because of money?

33
00:01:50,219 --> 00:01:51,879
Or is someone going to make you
the Commissioner General?

34
00:01:52,549 --> 00:01:55,950
What kind of groundless accusation
are you making?

35
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:57,959
Dismiss him!

36
00:01:57,959 --> 00:01:59,620
Arrest him and
request for a warrant!

37
00:01:59,689 --> 00:02:01,629
- Yes, sir.
- You're under arrest...

38
00:02:01,629 --> 00:02:02,629
for assaulting a police officer
and spreading false information.

39
00:02:03,060 --> 00:02:04,400
I haven't spread it yet!

40
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:06,760
You are going to. On top of that,
you are also slandering the police.

41
00:02:07,099 --> 00:02:08,800
Do you even have
any honor left for me to slander?

42
00:02:09,370 --> 00:02:10,569
Come here, you jerk!

43
00:02:11,770 --> 00:02:13,710
- Stop it, sir.
- Do you know who I am?

44
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:17,610
- Who are you?
- I'm the superintendent, you jerk!

45
00:02:17,780 --> 00:02:19,009
Superintendent, my foot!

46
00:02:20,979 --> 00:02:22,379
Father!

47
00:02:25,150 --> 00:02:26,550
Salute.

48
00:02:29,789 --> 00:02:30,889
My nose is clogged.

49
00:02:31,759 --> 00:02:33,490
Sir, my nose is clogged.

50
00:02:34,289 --> 00:02:36,090
Please give me strong antibiotics.

51
00:02:36,629 --> 00:02:37,900
Sir, my nose is clogged.

52
00:02:39,729 --> 00:02:40,770
- Hey!
- Hey!

53
00:02:42,129 --> 00:02:43,270
- Call an ambulance!
- Let me go.

54
00:02:43,270 --> 00:02:44,969
- Go!
- Come here, you!

55
00:02:44,969 --> 00:02:46,770
Lock him up in the jail!

56
00:02:49,039 --> 00:02:50,680
Who assaulted whom?

57
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:52,240
He hit the detective in charge.

58
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:55,310
It was because he wasn't happy
with the investigation result.

59
00:02:55,379 --> 00:02:56,479
So you're saying...

60
00:02:57,319 --> 00:02:59,780
that the detective was beaten
by the priest,

61
00:03:00,020 --> 00:03:02,250
and the police requested a warrant
on the priest, right?

62
00:03:02,389 --> 00:03:03,419
That's right.

63
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,360
I heard...

64
00:03:07,060 --> 00:03:09,259
the detective's nose bled
in a butterfly shape.

65
00:03:09,830 --> 00:03:13,129
The two men are causing
so much trouble.

66
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:15,729
Remove the ceiling,

67
00:03:15,729 --> 00:03:17,800
and install air purifying system
all over the place.

68
00:03:18,039 --> 00:03:20,099
Our kids with bright future
shouldn't inhale fine dust.

69
00:03:21,939 --> 00:03:23,979
- Excuse me, sir.
- Yes, ma'am?

70
00:03:24,780 --> 00:03:27,349
Our kids and I don't understand...

71
00:03:27,349 --> 00:03:29,479
the situation.

72
00:03:30,819 --> 00:03:32,719
This is what Father Lee
and I agreed upon...

73
00:03:32,849 --> 00:03:34,590
a long time ago.

74
00:03:34,849 --> 00:03:37,889
We decided that I'd take care
of this place and the other one...

75
00:03:37,889 --> 00:03:38,889
once Father Lee passes away.

76
00:03:39,159 --> 00:03:42,689
No. I've never heard of it.

77
00:03:42,759 --> 00:03:45,129
Of course you haven't.
But it's true.

78
00:03:45,759 --> 00:03:47,129
Father Lee...

79
00:03:47,199 --> 00:03:49,870
was transparent with the management
of our orphanage, and...

80
00:03:49,870 --> 00:03:51,270
Hello, children.

81
00:03:51,699 --> 00:03:55,039
I'll make this place nice
for you all to live in.

82
00:03:55,310 --> 00:03:57,740
I'll get you a lot of toys
and school supplies.

83
00:03:58,439 --> 00:03:59,539
Got it?

84
00:04:04,219 --> 00:04:05,379
Do I look scary?

85
00:04:06,949 --> 00:04:09,620
Ma'am, why don't you
get them some pizza?

86
00:04:09,889 --> 00:04:13,560
Don't buy something cheap.
Buy one with beef. What's it called?

87
00:04:13,629 --> 00:04:15,830
Right. Get the steak combination.

88
00:04:16,189 --> 00:04:17,199
Take it.

89
00:04:17,199 --> 00:04:18,230
- Wait.
- Take it.

90
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:20,500
Buy them a lot, okay?

91
00:04:22,899 --> 00:04:24,970
(Pharmacy)

92
00:04:26,370 --> 00:04:28,370
He could've broken my nose.

93
00:04:28,370 --> 00:04:29,910
My nose is the signature
of my features.

94
00:04:34,449 --> 00:04:36,779
I let my guard down
because he's a priest.

95
00:04:37,279 --> 00:04:40,250
If he weren't a priest,
when he attacked me,

96
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:42,519
I could've lightly avoided
his punch to the right...

97
00:04:42,589 --> 00:04:44,019
and hit him with my wrist snap only.

98
00:04:44,019 --> 00:04:45,389
I could've counterattacked him.

99
00:04:45,889 --> 00:04:46,889
Like Floyd Mayweather.

100
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:49,129
Let me ask you this again.

101
00:04:49,930 --> 00:04:52,230
Is the investigation result of
Father Lee absolutely true?

102
00:04:53,029 --> 00:04:55,930
Of course, we investigated him
in secret for months.

103
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:58,470
But some things just don't add up.

104
00:04:58,470 --> 00:04:59,740
I feel like it needs
to be reinvestigated.

105
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:01,939
You're so frustrating.

106
00:05:02,170 --> 00:05:03,509
Trust your senior colleague's words.

107
00:05:04,839 --> 00:05:06,079
If the investigation result...

108
00:05:06,079 --> 00:05:08,050
is not true,

109
00:05:09,509 --> 00:05:11,180
I'm going to quit my job.

110
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:13,449
I don't care
if it's a stable job for life.

111
00:05:15,250 --> 00:05:17,689
Those who say such things
work hard for over 30 years.

112
00:05:29,029 --> 00:05:33,670
(We'll work hard for our citizens
with warm hearts.)

113
00:05:38,810 --> 00:05:40,709
Are you Prosecutor Park Kyeong Seon?

114
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:42,279
Yes.

115
00:05:42,449 --> 00:05:44,120
I'm Lee Myeong Su, the team leader
of Violent Crimes Team.

116
00:05:50,220 --> 00:05:51,589
Please remove your nose hair
before working.

117
00:05:51,589 --> 00:05:53,089
You deal with civil complaints also.

118
00:05:55,430 --> 00:05:56,430
I'll go remove it right away.

119
00:06:02,329 --> 00:06:03,470
Where's the priest?

120
00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:06,439
- Detective Heo.
- Follow me.

121
00:06:13,339 --> 00:06:14,949
Goodness, Father.

122
00:06:18,949 --> 00:06:22,250
You're a very dynamic priest.

123
00:06:22,649 --> 00:06:23,920
What brings you here?

124
00:06:24,620 --> 00:06:26,819
I came to put you in jail.

125
00:06:26,889 --> 00:06:28,790
You came all the way here
to put me in jail?

126
00:06:29,060 --> 00:06:31,529
Of course.
It's a very rare opportunity...

127
00:06:31,930 --> 00:06:34,269
for a prosecutor to get a priest
locked up in jail.

128
00:06:34,399 --> 00:06:36,730
This is a very new experience.

129
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,839
Thanks to you, I'll also get to
experience something new.

130
00:06:38,970 --> 00:06:41,439
What? I don't think it'll be
so pleasant for you.

131
00:06:42,339 --> 00:06:44,240
You must not know
how much you'll suffer...

132
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:46,480
when you're dealing with
the Department of Justice.

133
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:48,410
I'll tell you how hard it gets
once I experience it firsthand.

134
00:06:48,649 --> 00:06:51,250
Are you doing this
because your faith is that strong?

135
00:06:51,250 --> 00:06:53,279
Or were you just born bold?

136
00:06:53,620 --> 00:06:55,819
If you must know,
it's a mixture of both.

137
00:06:57,490 --> 00:06:58,490
Unlock the door.

138
00:07:04,399 --> 00:07:06,259
Come outside. I need to talk to you.

139
00:07:08,970 --> 00:07:11,000
(Seoul Gudam Police Station,
Request for arrest warrant)

140
00:07:13,139 --> 00:07:15,310
You should get new ink.
Why is it so blurry?

141
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:26,120
- What are you doing?
- Isn't it obvious?

142
00:07:26,850 --> 00:07:28,790
I just saved you, Father.

143
00:07:30,660 --> 00:07:33,019
You save all the lost souls.

144
00:07:33,459 --> 00:07:36,089
And I save thoughtless law-breakers.

145
00:07:37,089 --> 00:07:38,160
It's nice, isn't it?

146
00:07:40,060 --> 00:07:41,100
So what's your point?

147
00:07:42,399 --> 00:07:44,040
You want me to call it even
and stay quiet?

148
00:07:44,170 --> 00:07:45,800
You're really good
at summarizing things.

149
00:07:46,839 --> 00:07:48,939
I'm doing you a huge favor.

150
00:07:49,509 --> 00:07:51,709
If you let me out,
I might cause a bigger mess.

151
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,310
Do you think you can deal with that?

152
00:07:53,310 --> 00:07:56,079
Nothing will change
regardless of what you do.

153
00:07:56,949 --> 00:07:57,949
Actually,
maybe one thing will change.

154
00:07:57,949 --> 00:07:59,750
Your life will become complicated.

155
00:08:01,949 --> 00:08:03,990
You're really good
at cursing a priest.

156
00:08:04,790 --> 00:08:06,990
Since nothing I do
will be able to change anything,

157
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:08,529
just tell me.

158
00:08:09,589 --> 00:08:11,100
Why did it have to be Father Lee?

159
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:13,660
I don't get the main point
of that question.

160
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,399
Why did it have to be Father Lee?

161
00:08:17,129 --> 00:08:19,040
Maybe it's because
he committed a crime.

162
00:08:22,910 --> 00:08:24,939
Up until a few days ago, he listened
to you confess your sins,

163
00:08:24,939 --> 00:08:26,579
pardoned you,
and treated you with love.

164
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:30,009
How can you be so nonchalant?

165
00:08:30,180 --> 00:08:31,550
Stop talking to me
like I'm your friend.

166
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:33,649
I'm a prosecutor.

167
00:08:34,350 --> 00:08:35,919
I'm very strict
when it comes to criminals.

168
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:37,789
You may go now.

169
00:08:38,590 --> 00:08:40,120
I'm going to make them
do an autopsy first...

170
00:08:41,529 --> 00:08:42,759
since that will prove everything.

171
00:08:46,799 --> 00:08:47,929
Keep this in mind.

172
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:50,940
If you get yourself in trouble
and show up in front of me again,

173
00:08:50,940 --> 00:08:53,200
I won't be easy on you
just because you're a priest.

174
00:08:58,779 --> 00:09:01,480
Why doesn't he listen
until I'm done talking?

175
00:09:03,850 --> 00:09:04,879
(Investigation Record
of Father Lee Young Jun's Case)

176
00:09:06,779 --> 00:09:09,389
Look at how huge
your nose has become.

177
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:13,460
You're a Violent Crimes detective.
Can't you defend yourself?

178
00:09:13,759 --> 00:09:16,330
I never imagined that
a priest would punch me.

179
00:09:16,330 --> 00:09:18,960
Are the investigation records
regarding Father Lee all legitimate?

180
00:09:19,059 --> 00:09:20,529
Yes, they're all legitimate.

181
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,830
- Be more confident.
- Yes, they're legitimate.

182
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,840
The woman who claimed
to have gotten raped.

183
00:09:24,899 --> 00:09:27,539
The administrative director who
helped him embezzle the offerings.

184
00:09:27,610 --> 00:09:29,970
- Do you have all the evidence?
- Pardon? Yes.

185
00:09:31,110 --> 00:09:34,110
Then can I trust all the evidence
and wrap up the case?

186
00:09:39,379 --> 00:09:42,250
The last thing you should be doing
is getting intimidated.

187
00:09:42,250 --> 00:09:44,360
I'll be the one getting in trouble
if you don't do things properly.

188
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:46,190
And I assure you,
it won't be a pretty sight.

189
00:09:46,789 --> 00:09:47,990
I'm sorry, ma'am.

190
00:09:50,090 --> 00:09:53,759
Why do you have to ruin the mood
by getting me so worked up?

191
00:09:55,299 --> 00:09:58,570
Stop being so clumsy, okay?

192
00:09:59,139 --> 00:10:01,340
- Especially you, big nose.
- Yes, ma'am.

193
00:10:06,110 --> 00:10:07,779
And I need you
to take care of something.

194
00:10:11,450 --> 00:10:14,190
What is this nonsense?
Why won't you let us take his body?

195
00:10:14,190 --> 00:10:16,090
We got orders
from the prosecution.

196
00:10:16,090 --> 00:10:17,220
They think the corpse's condition...

197
00:10:17,220 --> 00:10:18,559
- might get fabricated.
- Who in the world would...

198
00:10:19,059 --> 00:10:20,360
That's complete nonsense.

199
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:22,990
You can take his body...

200
00:10:22,990 --> 00:10:25,100
accompanied by the cops
on the morning of his funeral.

201
00:10:25,399 --> 00:10:28,269
And you need to hand in
where you're planning to bury him.

202
00:10:28,269 --> 00:10:29,769
What kind of nonsense is this?

203
00:10:29,769 --> 00:10:32,870
Forget all this.
We'll be taking his body.

204
00:10:33,299 --> 00:10:35,509
Father, things will get out of hand
if you do this.

205
00:10:35,509 --> 00:10:36,769
Father.

206
00:10:38,509 --> 00:10:40,009
We even need to stand guard
for stuff like this?

207
00:10:40,009 --> 00:10:43,309
(Chapel of Rest)

208
00:10:43,309 --> 00:10:45,419
Prosecutor Park gave us orders
to stand guard.

209
00:10:46,379 --> 00:10:48,220
Why did she release the priest
in the first place?

210
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:50,519
We had no reason
to keep him locked up.

211
00:10:51,019 --> 00:10:52,159
What do you mean
we had no reason?

212
00:10:52,860 --> 00:10:54,230
He broke my nose...

213
00:11:00,730 --> 00:11:01,769
He's here.

214
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:03,769
We have a code red situation
in front of the chapel of rest.

215
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:08,509
Didn't you hear anything
from the hospital administrator?

216
00:11:08,509 --> 00:11:11,509
I did, but I don't care.
So get out of my way!

217
00:11:13,539 --> 00:11:15,080
I really don't want to do this,

218
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:17,480
but you're really
giving me no choice.

219
00:11:17,649 --> 00:11:19,519
You should turn on the power first.

220
00:11:19,879 --> 00:11:20,889
Oh, right.

221
00:11:20,889 --> 00:11:23,889
Father, you're only making things
difficult for us.

222
00:11:23,889 --> 00:11:25,620
Am I supposed to care about that?

223
00:11:27,159 --> 00:11:28,289
Hurry up and get over here!

224
00:11:29,929 --> 00:11:32,299
Sir, what exactly is a code red?

225
00:11:32,299 --> 00:11:33,330
Code...

226
00:11:33,429 --> 00:11:35,600
Do you not watch American dramas?
Just try to understand the context.

227
00:11:35,929 --> 00:11:38,940
A priest is currently
trying to steal a corpse.

228
00:11:39,299 --> 00:11:41,710
Steal? Did you seriously
just say that? Get over here.

229
00:11:42,169 --> 00:11:43,169
Father.

230
00:11:47,480 --> 00:11:51,149
See? This is why I said it was
a code red situation. An emergency.

231
00:11:51,379 --> 00:11:53,820
You all should be careful.
This priest hits people.

232
00:11:53,950 --> 00:11:55,590
Most importantly, be careful
not to get your noses hurt.

233
00:11:55,750 --> 00:11:57,559
Brothers, please take a step back.

234
00:11:57,620 --> 00:11:59,490
You're the one
who should take a step back.

235
00:11:59,559 --> 00:12:01,759
You'll get yourself in a mess
if you keep doing this.

236
00:12:02,529 --> 00:12:04,559
Do you want to see which one of us
will end up in a bigger mess?

237
00:12:06,700 --> 00:12:08,970
Look at the way
he's flexing his fist.

238
00:12:10,029 --> 00:12:12,340
You should hold your anger.
Let's just go back for today.

239
00:12:12,399 --> 00:12:14,470
He's right, Father.
You should leave at least for today.

240
00:12:15,139 --> 00:12:16,139
No.

241
00:12:18,639 --> 00:12:19,909
If you come closer,
I'll pull the trigger.

242
00:12:20,509 --> 00:12:22,480
- I'm going to count to three.
- Go ahead and pull the trigger.

243
00:12:22,909 --> 00:12:24,720
Do you think you'll be able
to knock me out with that?

244
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:25,750
One.

245
00:12:26,950 --> 00:12:27,950
Two.

246
00:12:31,559 --> 00:12:32,590
Father.

247
00:12:54,179 --> 00:12:55,350
He got released?

248
00:12:55,950 --> 00:12:58,320
Yes, the prosecutor in charge
released him.

249
00:12:58,679 --> 00:13:00,850
Why would they let that lout free?

250
00:13:01,049 --> 00:13:02,149
Who's the prosecutor in charge?

251
00:13:02,620 --> 00:13:04,419
She gets direct orders
from Chief Prosecutor Kang.

252
00:13:05,389 --> 00:13:06,590
Chief Prosecutor Kang?

253
