00:27:03,160 --> 00:27:04,859
But it could be
because of his old age.

515
00:27:05,660 --> 00:27:07,000
What do you think?

516
00:27:07,329 --> 00:27:09,500
I think the former one
sounds more plausible.

517
00:27:10,700 --> 00:27:11,769
A bruise made because
he was grabbed by someone.

518
00:27:12,599 --> 00:27:14,069
Can we get a warrant
with this much information?

519
00:27:14,740 --> 00:27:16,809
We would've gotten one
already by the book.

520
00:27:17,440 --> 00:27:20,680
But they're scheming the whole thing
and even guarding the corpse.

521
00:27:21,609 --> 00:27:23,210
It doesn't seem like a small case.

522
00:27:25,980 --> 00:27:27,380
What's taking them so long?

523
00:27:27,650 --> 00:27:28,819
Who?

524
00:27:30,089 --> 00:27:31,690
The guy who's supposed to
move the corpse.

525
00:27:32,059 --> 00:27:33,720
It's been over 10 minutes already,
but he's still not here yet.

526
00:27:35,160 --> 00:27:36,190
10 minutes?
